ummary":"The same L/N/M context math is implemented with very different local styles across related files","related_files":["build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py"],"evidence":["`build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py` lines 139-150 computes `L_t` and `N_t` with Python loops and repeated `iloc` slices over the output frame.","`calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py` lines 88-98 repeats that same slice-heavy loop pattern almost verbatim.","`calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py` lines 137-145 computes the same idea directly with shifted arrays, making the sibling implementations look like unrelated local inventions instead of one consistent pattern."],"suggestion":"Choose one direct implementation for context-window math, preferably a small shared helper that takes a foul vector and returns `L_t`, `N_t`, and `M_t`. Replace the slice-heavy inline loops in the single-game scripts with that helper so related modules use the same local logic.","confidence":"medium","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"duplicated_possession_logic"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["Script-first development led each analysis file to rebuild the same low-level possession logic instead of consolidating it once.","Related modules evolved separately, so helper extraction style drifted between vectorized and slice-heavy implementations."],"likely_symptoms":["repeated_possession_internals","context_logic_style_drift"],"possible_false_positives":[]}}
